Dark matter affects flight of space probes
For years, a mysterious phenomenon of research has caused a lack of advice: Dark matter influences the speed of space probes during so-called swing-by manoeuvres.
Experts fear that the general theory of relativity of Albert Einstein could not be quite right.
Nearly 18 years the space probe "Ulysses" flew through space.
